GEO,Alaverdi,Georgia,ARM,(Armenian border),Armenia,internal,220,1,~80,150,100,0.03,,150/100,,operational NTC,existing,—,,,"220 kV Alaverdi tie DOES transmit power (~128 GWh AM→GE in 2025, mainly winter), so Operating=Yes per ""transmitting today"" definition. GE (IPS) and AM (Iran-sync) are in different synchronous zones, so NO parallel synchronous operation — flows are radial/limited. Planned CTN B2B at Ayrum would enable proper exchange. Also two small 110 kV ties (Lalvari, Ninotsminda). [conf: HIGH on flows]","NTC, specs, status & project: WB Regional Connectivity note 2025; GSE / UNESCAP 2024"
